               <physDesc>
                  <p> (1) tiruṉārāyaṇapurattile should correspond to Thirunarayanapuram in Tamil
                     Nadu (and should not correspond to the homonymous alternative name of Melkote
                     in Kerala)
                     (https://www.google.com/maps/place/Thirunarayanapuram,+Tamil+Nadu+621203,+India/@10.9931443,78.2142989,11.12z/data=!4m5!3m4!1s0x3baa4848ff143e7b:0xca9aee799b0ef50!8m2!3d10.9709713!4d78.32021).
                     (2) Note the peculiar way in which rṇa in paurṇamiyil [16v1]. (3) The date is
                     indeterminable because several days in the Gregorian calendar fit in: 6 March
                     1623, 2 March 1683 (next-day tithi and nakṣatra), 3 April 1863 (next-day tithi)
                     and, accepting small inaccuracies, also 27 February (it was the last day of the
                     month of Māci, thus not Paṅkuṉi yet) and 27 March 1743 (tithi and nakṣatra do
                     not overlap for a few hours). </p>
               </physDesc>
